### Step 5: Enhance the Canvas Card Accent (canvaspreview.css)

The existing sage border accent is subtle. Strengthen it slightly by adding a top-bar accent that acts as a colored stripe at the top of the card, reinforcing the "creative artifact" feel.

Add after the badge styles:

```css
/* ── Canvas Card Top Accent Bar ── */
.cards.is-canvas-card::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(
        90deg,
        var(--accent-sage),
        color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-sage) 60%, var(--accent-purple))
    );
    border-radius: 12px 12px 0 0;
    z-index: 2;
    opacity: 0.7;
    transition: opacity 0.25s ease;
}

.cards.is-canvas-card:hover::before {
    opacity: 1;
}
```

This creates a thin sage-to-purple gradient bar at the top of canvas cards. It is visible above the `CanvasPreview` component since the pseudo-element has `z-index: 2`. The gradient subtly ties into the remix button's purple accent, creating visual cohesion between the card type indicator and the remix action.

